Prep the veggies: Wash and dry all produce. Bring a large #pot of salted water to
a boil. Halve, peel and dice the @Yellow Onion{1}(halved, peeled and diced). Peel
and finely dice the @Carrots{2}(peeled and finely diced). Mince or grate the
@Garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Roughly chop the @Button Mushrooms{4%oz}(roughly chopped).

Cook the veggies: Heat a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%tsp} in a large #pan over
medium heat. Add the onion and carrots to the #pan and cook, tossing for about
~{5%minutes}, until softened. Add the mushrooms to the #pan and cook for another
~{5%minutes}, until softened. Add the garlic and cook for an additional
~{30%seconds}, until fragrant. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Cook the sausage and the spaghetti: Meanwhile, remove the @Sweet Italian Pork Sausage{18%oz}
from the casings. Once the veggies are softened, add the @Spaghetti{12%oz}
to the boiling water and cook for ~{10%minutes}, until al dente. Drain. Add the
sausage to the #pan and cook, breaking up the meat into pieces, until browned.

Simmer the Bolognese: Add the @Crushed Tomatoes{2%box} and @Beef Stock Concentrate{1}
to the #pan and simmer for ~{4-5%minutes}, until thickened. Season to taste with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

> If the sauce becomes too thick, add a bit of water.

Add the spinach: Stir the @Spinach{10%oz} into the Bolognese to wilt. Season to
taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Plate and serve: Serve the quick sausage Bolognese on a bed of spaghetti. Tear
the @Basil{1/2%oz}(torn) leaves over top and sprinkle with
@Parmesan Cheese{1/2%cup}. Enjoy!